WEBVTT

00:19.770 --> 00:22.188
FARNSWORTH:
Good news, everyone!

00:22.272 --> 00:25.983
We've been hired to make
our 100th delivery.

00:26.068 --> 00:27.944
(ALL CHEERING)
One hundred!

00:28.028 --> 00:29.487
That's almost
10 per year.

00:29.780 --> 00:31.531
This calls for a party, baby.

00:31.615 --> 00:35.952
I'm ordering 100 kegs,
100 hookers and
100 Elvis impersonators

00:36.036 --> 00:39.622
who aren't above
a little hooking,
should the occasion arise.

00:42.876 --> 00:45.044
Be very gentle, folks.

00:45.129 --> 00:48.047
This is the soufflé
you're delivering
to Mrs. Astor.

00:48.132 --> 00:51.968
Oh, my God, it's Elzar!
Hi, Elzar!
Great soufflé, Elzar!

00:52.052 --> 00:55.221
Whatever you do,
don't drop it.

00:55.305 --> 00:58.391
See, Mrs. Astor takes
nitroglycerine for her heart,

00:58.475 --> 01:02.270
and being a class act,
she prefers it
in soufflé form.

01:04.647 --> 01:06.023
(SOFTLY) Bam!
(ALL GASP)

01:06.108 --> 01:10.027
To prevent the soufflé
from exploding,
Bender will carry it.

01:10.112 --> 01:12.488
He's gyroscopically stable.

01:16.910 --> 01:18.494
(ALL EXCLAIMING)

01:27.921 --> 01:29.422
(ALL GRUNTING)

01:31.008 --> 01:37.013
Look! Mrs. Astor's mansion,
just across
that rickety rope bridge.

01:37.681 --> 01:38.848
(WIND HOWLING)

01:39.683 --> 01:42.268
Wow, it's ricketier
than it looks.

01:42.352 --> 01:44.270
You better try
to jump it, Bender.

01:44.354 --> 01:47.607
Okay, let me back up
for a running start.

01:56.241 --> 01:57.617
Here I go!

02:01.663 --> 02:03.039
(SCREAMING)

02:04.708 --> 02:06.125
(RINGING DOORBELL)

02:07.127 --> 02:11.047
I shall inform Mrs. Astor
that the circus is in town.

02:11.882 --> 02:13.800
Your soufflé, madam.

02:13.884 --> 02:16.219
I shall take it here,
under my fork.

02:17.763 --> 02:18.846
(EXCLAIMING SOFTLY)

02:21.809 --> 02:22.934
(ALL SHUDDERING)

02:32.319 --> 02:33.528
(EXCLAIMING)

02:34.404 --> 02:36.030
Where's the exploding?

02:36.281 --> 02:39.784
One does not explode
in Mrs. Astor's face.

02:39.868 --> 02:42.745
I couldn't eat
another bite.
Hobsie?

02:42.871 --> 02:44.330
(ALL BARKING)

02:45.457 --> 02:46.833
(EXPLOSION)

02:47.000 --> 02:49.377
Well done, sir.
Have you a name?

02:49.461 --> 02:52.255
Hubert Farnsworth,
at your service.

02:52.339 --> 02:55.466
A Farnsworth, you say?
Well, if I'm not mistaken,

02:55.551 --> 02:58.845
the Farnsworths have been
in New New York
for almost 200 years.

02:58.929 --> 03:00.596
Yes, I have.

03:00.681 --> 03:01.764
And I'm his uncle.

03:01.849 --> 03:04.433
How charmingly
unconventional.

03:04.518 --> 03:06.352
I can eat a hot dog
underwater.

03:06.436 --> 03:09.355
Say, would you Farnsworths
care to be my guests tomorrow

03:09.439 --> 03:11.399
at the Astor
Endowment Fundraiser?

03:11.483 --> 03:13.359
All the best families
will be there.

03:13.443 --> 03:15.111
We can take them.

03:24.872 --> 03:29.250
On April 10, 2912,
my late husband and I

03:29.334 --> 03:32.670
set off down Fifth Avenue
aboard the Land Titanic,

03:32.754 --> 03:36.048
the largest
street-going vessel
ever built.

03:36.133 --> 03:40.887
Just four days
into her maiden voyage,
as we approached 32nd Street,

03:40.971 --> 03:44.432
the land liner
struck a mailbox
and went down.

03:46.226 --> 03:51.731
2,000 souls
were lost that day,
including my dear husband.

03:51.815 --> 03:55.276
In loving memory,
I established
the Mr. Astor Endowment,

03:55.360 --> 03:59.572
which this year supports
the United Mutant
Scholarship Fund.

03:59.656 --> 04:01.365
(GUESTS APPLAUDING)

04:01.450 --> 04:03.743
Mutants?
That's the kind of thing
you are.

04:03.827 --> 04:06.162
Shh. You know mutants
aren't allowed
on the surface.

04:06.246 --> 04:09.665
If anyone asks,
say I'm an alien,
remember?

04:09.750 --> 04:11.584
Right. You gonna
finish that roll?

04:11.668 --> 04:12.668
Shh.

04:12.753 --> 04:18.382
Now, a short film about
those pitiable creatures
so in need of our charity.

04:19.760 --> 04:23.888
NARRATOR: Far beneath
the everyday rumble
of limousines and poodle feet,

04:23.972 --> 04:26.098
there toil
a downtrodden people

04:26.183 --> 04:29.352
even less well off
than the upper middle class.

04:29.436 --> 04:31.812
The noble sewer mutants.

04:31.897 --> 04:35.441
For, you see, generations
of exposure to toxic sewage

04:35.525 --> 04:38.945
mutated them
into horrific monsters!

04:39.029 --> 04:40.029
(BOTH GASP)

04:40.113 --> 04:41.155
Shut up.

04:41.239 --> 04:44.492
NARRATOR:
These industrious,
uh, people, I guess,

04:44.576 --> 04:47.286
maintain the various pipes
and poop chutes

04:47.371 --> 04:50.706
that keep decent,
above-ground society
functioning.

04:51.416 --> 04:54.669
And where do these
proud toileteers
learn their menial skills?

04:54.753 --> 04:55.795
(MEOWS)

04:55.879 --> 04:57.588
At Brown University,

04:57.673 --> 05:01.509
the nation's
premiere institution
of lower learning.

05:01.593 --> 05:03.970
So please, give generously,

05:04.054 --> 05:07.473
knowing some poor helpless
mutant will thank you.

05:07.557 --> 05:10.059
Not in person, thank God.

05:12.646 --> 05:14.021
Well, that
was disturbing.

05:14.106 --> 05:17.191
I understand, dear.
They are hideous.

05:17.275 --> 05:20.528
Look, I guess you mean well,
but isn't that university

05:20.612 --> 05:23.614
just a tax-deductible
sewer-cleaning service?

05:23.699 --> 05:27.702
My dear, that school
is about much more
than sewer pipes.

05:27.786 --> 05:28.828
Really?

05:28.912 --> 05:31.664
It's also about keeping
those filthy things busy.

05:31.748 --> 05:35.501
There are thousands of them
down there,
breeding like rats.

05:35.585 --> 05:37.670
My great uncle
once saw a rat.

05:37.754 --> 05:39.088
If we don't
keep them busy,

05:39.172 --> 05:43.676
they'll start jabbering
about equal rights
in their ill-bred manner.

05:43.760 --> 05:44.844
Let's go.

05:44.928 --> 05:47.847
If I say one more thing,
I might say it
with my evening boot.

05:47.931 --> 05:50.266
Well! Rarely have I never!

05:50.726 --> 05:54.353
Please, don't blame Leela.
She's just a little ill-bred.

05:54.438 --> 05:56.355
You know how mutants are.

05:56.440 --> 05:57.940
(ALL GASPING)

05:58.692 --> 06:01.360
Your companion
is a mutant?

06:01.445 --> 06:04.113
(SOFTLY)
But if anyone asks,
say she's an alien.

06:04.197 --> 06:06.282
Help! Police!

06:08.076 --> 06:10.202
You may have
eluded the authorities,

06:10.287 --> 06:13.039
but don't nothing
get past Mrs. Astor.

06:17.085 --> 06:18.294
(GRUNTING)

06:18.670 --> 06:20.046
What's going to
happen to me?

06:20.130 --> 06:22.840
Permanent
deportation,
you mutant.

06:22.924 --> 06:26.552
You going downtown,
baby. Way down.

06:26.636 --> 06:28.012
(ELECTRIC BLEEP)
(SCREAMING)

06:33.894 --> 06:35.269
(SCREAMING)

06:35.854 --> 06:37.146
Incoming!

06:39.941 --> 06:40.941
Thanks, Colonel.

06:41.026 --> 06:43.319
Just doing
my job, ma'am.

06:47.699 --> 06:49.158
(RINGING DOORBELL)

06:49.659 --> 06:50.659
(SOBBING)

06:50.744 --> 06:56.665
Mom, Dad, I can't believe
I have to spend the rest
of my life in this hellhole.

06:57.459 --> 06:58.459
I'm sorry.

06:58.543 --> 07:00.127
It's okay, sweetie.

07:00.212 --> 07:04.590
Now that you're here,
this hellhole feels more
like a nice, regular hole.

07:04.674 --> 07:06.926
What do you say
we go get
some sewer coffee,

07:07.010 --> 07:09.512
sewer cake and
Safeway ice cream.

07:13.850 --> 07:15.142
(SPUTTERING)

07:15.227 --> 07:17.728
Well, the bottom's
all stocked
with cheap stuff.

07:17.813 --> 07:19.480
Who's in the mood
to party?

07:19.564 --> 07:21.023
Whoo!

07:21.149 --> 07:22.149
(GROANS)

07:22.234 --> 07:25.111
Poor Leela. I feel
like I ruined her life.

07:25.195 --> 07:26.612
You did ruin her life.

07:26.696 --> 07:27.905
You might be
right, Hermes.

07:27.989 --> 07:28.989
I am right.

07:29.074 --> 07:31.575
I almost feel like
we should do something
to help her.

07:31.660 --> 07:33.369
We should do something!

07:33.453 --> 07:36.080
I don't care
what you say, Hermes.
Let's go.

07:37.249 --> 07:40.167
Oh, mighty Mayor,
we're here
about Turanga Leela.

07:40.252 --> 07:41.877
You mean Leela?
Right.

07:41.962 --> 07:44.672
I mean, sure, she's a mutant,
we've known that for years,

07:44.756 --> 07:47.591
but we kept it secret
'cause she's a fine,
upstanding...

07:47.676 --> 07:50.803
Wait. You knowingly
attempted to harbor a mutant?

07:50.887 --> 07:52.638
We did
harbor a mutant!

07:52.722 --> 07:53.722
Uh-oh.

07:54.558 --> 07:56.976
Look, Leela,
there's Old Filthful.

07:58.520 --> 08:00.104
(ALL EXCLAIMING)

08:01.356 --> 08:02.356
Urgh!

08:02.440 --> 08:04.316
And there's the
West Side Pipeway.

08:04.401 --> 08:08.154
If those guys slack off
for even a second,
it could explode.

08:08.238 --> 08:10.489
Hey, guys!
This is my daughter, Leela.

08:10.574 --> 08:12.116
Hey.
How you doing?

08:12.200 --> 08:13.576
(SCREAMING)

08:15.745 --> 08:17.830
Well, they're with
the chuds now.

08:17.914 --> 08:20.666
These conditions
are deplorable.

08:20.750 --> 08:24.879
I swear, I hate
every single person
on the surface

08:24.963 --> 08:26.881
for making us
live like this.

08:26.965 --> 08:27.965
(GROANING)

08:29.259 --> 08:30.384
(GASPS) Leela!

08:30.468 --> 08:31.802
What are you
doing here?

08:31.887 --> 08:36.097
We were sentenced
to two weeks in the sewer
for harboring a mutant.

08:39.269 --> 08:41.270
$3 at the drugstore.

08:41.354 --> 08:43.772
I'm so sorry
I ratted you out,

08:43.857 --> 08:45.733
but, you know,
after two weeks down here,

08:45.817 --> 08:48.652
I'll truly understand
the plight of
the mutant people.

08:48.737 --> 08:50.029
How dare you.

08:50.113 --> 08:53.365
You want to
understand something?
Look at that lake.

08:53.450 --> 08:55.534
One dip
in that toxic muck

08:55.619 --> 08:58.454
and your DNA will be
permanently mutated.

08:58.538 --> 09:00.956
You'll grow a camel hump
or a Zoidberg face.

09:01.041 --> 09:02.041
Urgh!

09:02.125 --> 09:04.168
You want to know
what it's like
to be a mutant?

09:04.252 --> 09:06.337
Jump in
and go for a swim.

09:06.421 --> 09:10.216
I would,
but I ate a bunch of
potato salad, so...

09:10.300 --> 09:14.386
Yeah, that's what I thought.
You are all surface.

09:16.348 --> 09:17.348
Yeah.

09:20.101 --> 09:21.101
Hmm.

09:21.186 --> 09:24.563
Fry! Hermes!
Where my humans at?

09:24.648 --> 09:27.358
Ah, who cares? It is on.

09:27.442 --> 09:29.068
(DOORBELL RINGING)

09:29.819 --> 09:31.445
Hey, hey, hey.

09:31.529 --> 09:33.030
(ALL WHOOPING)

09:33.156 --> 09:35.032
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

09:35.825 --> 09:39.453
I trust the orgy pit
has been scraped and buttered?

09:39.537 --> 09:42.122
You know it.
And there's
mini quiches, too.

09:43.667 --> 09:44.667
(SHIVERING)

09:44.751 --> 09:48.504
It's getting cold and smelly.
My Odor-Eaters
are going critical.

09:50.548 --> 09:53.008
Maybe we could plotz
in that giant cockle.

09:54.928 --> 09:57.596
AMY: Shmeepers,
it's the Land Titanic,

09:57.681 --> 10:00.975
the biggest and onlyest
land boat ever constructed.

10:02.644 --> 10:03.644
(WHISTLES)

10:03.728 --> 10:06.063
This was
one hell of a bus.

10:06.147 --> 10:10.442
Well, everyone
debone a bunk
and get some shut-eye.

10:10.527 --> 10:12.528
Zoidberg,
show some respect.

10:12.612 --> 10:16.156
This is a sacred shrine
to the thousands
who lost their lives.

10:16.241 --> 10:18.200
AMY: Hey, I found a safe.

10:18.660 --> 10:20.035
(GRUNTING)

10:20.537 --> 10:21.620
It's coming loose.

10:21.705 --> 10:24.873
Hand me some more
of that cruise director.

10:28.003 --> 10:29.461
(ALL GASPING)

10:30.547 --> 10:32.840
The original
passenger manifest.

10:32.924 --> 10:35.759
Spreadsheets were
so elegant back then.

10:35.844 --> 10:37.761
Just one other item.

10:37.846 --> 10:42.933
It's jewelry. Jewelry!
It's jewelry, people!

10:43.018 --> 10:46.103
It's a priceless
quantum-force gemerald.

10:49.607 --> 10:51.150
What's that
enscribbled on it?

10:52.193 --> 10:54.153
"My dear Mrs. Astor.

10:54.237 --> 10:57.656
"My love for you
is as unsinkable
as this land ship

10:57.741 --> 11:00.492
"and as brilliant
as this stone.

11:00.577 --> 11:02.244
"Dictated but not read,
Mr. Astor."

11:02.537 --> 11:03.620
Aw.

11:03.705 --> 11:06.081
That's so valuable.

11:06.166 --> 11:10.502
Yeah, I'll never
have love like that.
Leela hates me now.

11:10.587 --> 11:12.921
Did you guys know
I have a crush on Leela?

11:16.051 --> 11:19.762
What's the matter, Leela?
You've hardly
touched your toilet clams.

11:19.888 --> 11:20.929
(SIGHS)

11:21.014 --> 11:23.182
Maybe I was too harsh
on Fry.

11:23.266 --> 11:25.225
He didn't ruin my life
on purpose.

11:25.310 --> 11:27.561
Things will work out,
honey. Now, here.

11:27.645 --> 11:30.647
Have some more
of what looks like
lemonade.

11:31.691 --> 11:33.567
(CLUB MUSIC PLAYING)

11:33.735 --> 11:37.571
MAN: (SINGING)
We can dip left slide right
all night

11:37.697 --> 11:40.699
It's time to be wild

11:40.784 --> 11:43.077
Freestyle

11:43.953 --> 11:45.371
It's on and poppin'

11:45.455 --> 11:47.581
Ain't no stoppin'
Us from rockin'

11:47.665 --> 11:49.583
From tonight to ten o'clock

11:49.667 --> 11:53.337
Bender, I've been to
wang dang doodles
all up and down the galaxy,

11:53.421 --> 11:56.465
but this is the dangest wang
I ever doodled.

11:56.549 --> 11:57.800
Oh, yeah!

11:58.385 --> 11:59.843
Come on, baby,
let's do it!

11:59.928 --> 12:01.845
Shake your booty, baby.
Come on! Yeah!

12:01.971 --> 12:03.305
(GRUNTING)

12:13.024 --> 12:15.109
This beat bangs
Here's my chance

12:15.193 --> 12:17.444
Come on, girl, let's go,
I can't...

12:17.529 --> 12:18.570
(MUSIC STOPS)

12:18.655 --> 12:23.492
Get out! Get out!
It's not fun anymore!
I want to be alone!

12:23.576 --> 12:24.660
Alone with me?

12:24.744 --> 12:26.495
I said scram, grapey!

12:27.122 --> 12:28.122
(GULPING)

12:45.682 --> 12:46.682
(GASPS)

12:46.766 --> 12:49.101
Fry? What are you doing?

12:49.185 --> 12:50.185
You were right.

12:50.270 --> 12:52.521
I don't know
what it's like
to be a mutant.

12:52.605 --> 12:53.981
But I want to know.

12:54.065 --> 12:56.775
Wait. I never
meant for you to...

12:56.860 --> 12:58.193
Oh, no!

13:01.448 --> 13:03.407
Fry! Fry!

13:03.867 --> 13:05.701
No! No!

13:09.456 --> 13:10.789
Any effect?

13:10.874 --> 13:11.915
(SCREAMING)

13:12.000 --> 13:13.333
(RETCHING)

13:13.418 --> 13:16.170
Sorry. I tried to scream
but I barfed.

13:21.217 --> 13:22.259
(SCREAMS)

13:22.343 --> 13:25.179
I think I'm knowing
what it's like
to be a mutant.

13:25.763 --> 13:27.764
So what's with all
the screaming?

13:27.891 --> 13:29.349
Hey, guys.
(ALL GASPING)

13:29.434 --> 13:30.767
(ALL RETCHING)

13:30.852 --> 13:35.314
Fry, this is the
stupidest, sweetest thing
you've ever done.

13:35.398 --> 13:37.524
And you know,
maybe now, together,

13:37.609 --> 13:40.235
we can be an inspiration
to other mutants.

13:40.320 --> 13:41.820
I hope so, Leela.

13:41.905 --> 13:45.032
Aw. Come here.
Let me
give you a kiss.

13:46.493 --> 13:47.743
Hug.

13:47.827 --> 13:49.036
Handshake.

13:49.120 --> 13:50.204
I'll text you.

13:50.288 --> 13:52.039
(MUTANTS CHEERING)

13:52.415 --> 13:56.460
My fellow mutants,
until recently,
I dwelt on the surface,

13:56.544 --> 13:59.046
where a man
can gaze up at the sky
in wonder

13:59.130 --> 14:01.632
without a wet clump
falling in his mouth.

14:01.716 --> 14:02.716
MALE MUTANT:
We can do that, too.

14:02.800 --> 14:03.842
(PLOPPING)

14:03.927 --> 14:06.136
Who's ready to fight
for equality?

14:07.180 --> 14:10.724
The devolution revolution
has begun!

14:10.808 --> 14:14.603
Beautiful mutants,
please welcome Devo!

14:14.687 --> 14:16.355
(MUTANTS CHEERING)

14:17.774 --> 14:19.191
Hello, Sewer City.

14:21.194 --> 14:25.197
As longtime mutants ourselves,
we support
your righteous struggle,

14:25.281 --> 14:27.574
and we'll do anything
we can for you!

14:27.659 --> 14:29.076
Play Whip lt!
No.

14:29.160 --> 14:30.410
Play the other one.

14:30.495 --> 14:32.496
(PLAYING BEAUTIFUL WORLD)

14:33.206 --> 14:35.916
It's a beautiful world
we live in

14:36.751 --> 14:39.086
A sweet romantic place

14:40.129 --> 14:42.923
Beautiful people everywhere

14:43.633 --> 14:46.301
The way they show they care

14:46.511 --> 14:48.679
Makes me want to say

14:49.305 --> 14:51.014
It's a beautiful world

14:51.099 --> 14:52.432
Ooh! (LAUGHING)

14:52.517 --> 14:57.729
It's a beautiful world

14:58.648 --> 14:59.606
For you

14:59.691 --> 15:01.066
(ALL GASPING)

15:02.068 --> 15:06.572
For you

15:08.825 --> 15:10.284
Now that we've got
their attention,

15:10.368 --> 15:12.369
it's time to hit them
where they sit

15:12.453 --> 15:16.832
by bending the
West Side Pipeway to return
all sewage to the surface.

15:19.586 --> 15:23.255
But who could
possibly bend
such a huge pipe?

15:23.339 --> 15:24.381
(SOBBING)

15:24.465 --> 15:27.926
So lonely.
Poor, sad Bender.

15:28.344 --> 15:30.012
Hey, buddy.
(GASPING)

15:31.180 --> 15:32.848
What the heck?

15:34.475 --> 15:38.437
Bend it! Bend it! Bend it!

15:38.521 --> 15:39.855
(GRUNTING)

15:47.947 --> 15:50.532
What goes down must back up.

15:50.950 --> 15:52.576
(SEWAGE BUBBLING)

15:56.372 --> 15:58.040
(VEHICLES HONKING)

16:00.209 --> 16:04.588
Yucks. I picked the wrong day
to wear my new Crocses.

16:04.672 --> 16:08.759
Prepare to storm the surface
for the Million Mutant March!

16:11.262 --> 16:12.554
Move out, Fry.

16:12.639 --> 16:15.474
We need our most
disgusting mutant
leading the charge.

16:15.558 --> 16:18.310
I'll meet you up there.
I need to check out
something first.

16:18.394 --> 16:20.520
Okay. Vyolet,
you're up front.

16:20.605 --> 16:21.605
Hey!

16:23.232 --> 16:26.652
MRS. ASTOR:
Mayor, this sewer debacle
has gone on long enough.

16:26.736 --> 16:31.281
As your largest
campaign contributor,
I demand action!

16:31.366 --> 16:34.242
Very well.
$80 worth of action it is.

16:35.495 --> 16:36.495
Voilà.

16:36.579 --> 16:40.999
We simply pump
the fruits of our excretion
into Madison Cube Garden.

16:42.210 --> 16:44.920
Well, it seems
everything is under...

16:45.004 --> 16:46.004
(GASPING)

16:46.089 --> 16:47.798
(MUTANTS CLAMORING)

16:50.343 --> 16:51.468
Two!
Four!

16:51.552 --> 16:52.678
Six eyes!

16:52.762 --> 16:55.263
The mutant people
will arise!

16:55.348 --> 16:58.517
The segregation
of the mutant people
ends today.

16:58.601 --> 17:02.854
We demand equal rights,
equal access
to the surface,

17:02.939 --> 17:05.648
and the blood of
your first-born children.

17:05.775 --> 17:08.859
(SOFTLY) That's so
we have something to give up
in the negotiations.

17:08.944 --> 17:13.115
I've never been so moved,
and I see no reason
to begin now.

17:13.199 --> 17:17.493
Hobsie, flush those creatures
back down the hole
they crawled out of.

17:17.578 --> 17:19.663
Madam's sewage-seeking
missile.

17:21.457 --> 17:23.125
(GASPING)

17:39.976 --> 17:42.185
Let my people stay!

17:49.652 --> 17:50.777
Neat.

17:51.404 --> 17:53.238
Mrs. Astor,
deep in the sewer,

17:53.322 --> 17:55.699
we discovered the wreck
of the Land Titanic,

17:55.783 --> 17:57.576
on which your husband
land-drowned.

17:57.660 --> 18:00.787
Inside was something
that might interest you.

18:00.872 --> 18:05.292
The gemerald ring
my husband was to give me
in lieu of children.

18:05.376 --> 18:08.378
So what? I have a chandelier
in my car made of those.

18:08.463 --> 18:11.089
Not the gem.
This passenger manifest.

18:11.174 --> 18:13.216
It turns out
there were mutants
on that ship

18:13.301 --> 18:15.385
working below deck
in the sewage galley.

18:16.012 --> 18:17.053
Ma'am?

18:17.138 --> 18:20.056
I was just a young girl.

18:20.141 --> 18:22.601
Drain angels,
they called us.

18:22.685 --> 18:25.020
When the ship
started going down,

18:25.104 --> 18:29.065
my mother grabbed me
and made for
the nearest life-car.

18:31.360 --> 18:35.530
But the places were all taken
by surface passengers.

18:35.615 --> 18:38.241
As my mother held me tight,

18:38.326 --> 18:42.829
I suddenly felt
the gentle tap of a cane
on my face.

18:42.914 --> 18:47.667
I turned to see
the kindly smile
of Mr. Astor.

18:59.514 --> 19:02.224
Thanks to your
husband's humanity,

19:02.308 --> 19:07.562
I lived to raise
my own daughter, and she,
a daughter in turn.

19:07.647 --> 19:10.398
Mom, why have I
never heard this?

19:10.483 --> 19:12.192
(WHISPERING)
My mother's nuts.

19:12.276 --> 19:13.902
I beg you,
Mrs. Astor,

19:13.986 --> 19:16.655
if you truly want to
honor your
husband's memory,

19:16.739 --> 19:20.200
treat these people
with dignity, as he did.

19:20.284 --> 19:23.745
Oh, he was
a dear man, Mr. Astor.

19:24.413 --> 19:27.499
Randall, let's grant
these mutants their freedom.

19:27.583 --> 19:28.625
Okay.

19:28.709 --> 19:30.377
(MUTANTS CHEERING)

19:30.461 --> 19:32.212
Are we not men now?

19:32.296 --> 19:35.048
I'm 40% potato,
but close enough.

19:35.132 --> 19:36.716
Thank you, Fry.

19:36.801 --> 19:39.594
I think maybe I can
stomach that kiss now.

19:40.096 --> 19:41.429
(RETCHING)

19:44.767 --> 19:46.017
What the...

19:46.102 --> 19:48.144
Good afternoon.
I am Mr. Astor.

19:48.229 --> 19:50.313
I did not perish
that fateful day,

19:50.398 --> 19:52.774
but rather plummeted
into the toxic lake,

19:52.859 --> 19:55.026
where I mutated
and lived in solitude

19:55.111 --> 19:59.114
until this ruddy lad here
stepped into my mouth
and lodged there.

19:59.240 --> 20:02.242
Mister?
Is that really you?

20:02.535 --> 20:04.160
(EXCLAIMING WITH JOY)

20:04.287 --> 20:08.456
Hooray! A happy ending
for the rich people!

20:12.253 --> 20:16.256
Mom, Dad, Grandma,
this is where I work.

20:16.382 --> 20:17.591
Oh!

20:18.384 --> 20:19.801
Was there a fire?

20:19.886 --> 20:21.845
So, Bender,
how was the party?

20:21.929 --> 20:24.180
Only the greatest
party ever!

20:24.265 --> 20:26.641
I don't need to have
another party
in my whole life.

20:26.726 --> 20:28.518
I am partied out!

20:28.603 --> 20:30.478
Dang.
Sorry we missed it.

20:31.063 --> 20:35.233
We could have another one,
if it would make
you guys feel better.

20:35.318 --> 20:37.402
Really? No,
that's not necessary.

20:37.486 --> 20:38.904
Hit it, Bender!

20:39.113 --> 20:41.448
MAN: (SINGING)
Bend it, bend it

20:41.532 --> 20:43.450
Just a little bit

20:43.534 --> 20:45.702
And take it easy

20:45.828 --> 20:47.579
Show you're likin' it

20:47.663 --> 20:51.416
And, lover, you know
that we're gonna hit

20:51.500 --> 20:54.669
The heights 'cause
I'm sure
that we're made to fit

20:54.754 --> 20:57.714
Together, just like
pieces of a

20:57.798 --> 20:59.925
Jigsaw puzzle

21:00.009 --> 21:02.636
What's the hustle?

21:40.007 --> 21:41.007
ENGLISH - US - PSDH
